NORTHERN PACIFIC RAILWAY COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellant and Cross-Appellee, v. ADAMS COUNTY et al., Appellees and Cross-Appellants. No. 7120. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 23, 1933. L. B. Da Ponte, of Seattle, Wash., for appellant and cross-appellee. John A. Homer, Asst. Atty. Gen., for all appellees and cross-appellants except King, Benton and Yakima Counties. Robert M. Burgunder, of Seattle, Wash., for King County. Charles L. Powell, of Kennewick, Wash., for Benton County. O. Sandvig, of Yakima, Wash., for Yakima County.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal and cross-appeal (1 F. Supp. 163) dismissed without costs to either party; mandate forthwith.
